{"priority": "major", "kind": "bug", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/143/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/143.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/143/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/143/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/143/subt-commsclient-cant-handle-ros"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/143/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Reid Sawtell", "uuid": "{845ed98c-79aa-4771-ab0d-6d8424f27344}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B845ed98c-79aa-4771-ab0d-6d8424f27344%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B845ed98c-79aa-4771-ab0d-6d8424f27344%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/8a592422a10cc54f020efbc4d867c556d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsRS-6.png"}}, "nickname": "rsawtell", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:ba6a5dd6-99be-45af-a802-687b3318965a"}, "title": "SubT CommsClient Can't handle ros namespaces", "component": null, "votes": 1, "watches": 6, "content": {"raw": "All of the hardcoded paths in CommonTypes.hh are relative, so any instantiation of the comms client in a ros namespace automatically fails to connect to the broker. This didn\u2019t seem to be a problem in the past \\(eg: a month ago\\), but it is preventing us from using the comms package now because our controller is instantiated in a <group ns=\u201d\u2026\u201d> tag along with our other data processing nodes.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>All of the hardcoded paths in CommonTypes.hh are relative, so any instantiation of the comms client in a ros namespace automatically fails to connect to the broker. This didn\u2019t seem to be a problem in the past (eg: a month ago), but it is preventing us from using the comms package now because our controller is instantiated in a &lt;group ns=\u201d\u2026\u201d&gt; tag along with our other data processing nodes.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0/ca24bb11-4787-4b14-a20d-d91835e9bde2/128"}}, "nickname": "Nathan Koenig", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0"}, "state": "closed", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2019-08-01T20:45:59.037701+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2019-10-31T05:56:33.881155+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 143}